Got it. Here’s a clean, copy-pasteable table you can drop into Excel and review with your architect.

### Assumptions (from your data)

* **Doc count (current):** 1,365,563,219
* **Avg size per doc:** ~0.333 KB (≈ 3 docs ≈ 1 KB)
* **S1 storage per partition:** 160 GB
* **Price per SU (S1):** $245.28 / month
* **SU = Replicas × Partitions** (storage comes from **partitions**)

---

### Sizing & Cost Options

| Env                               | Tier | SUs | Replicas | Partitions | Storage GB (service) | Est. Max Docs (service) |   Fits 1.365B?  | Monthly Cost (USD) | Notes / Recommendation                            |
| --------------------------------- | ---- | --: | -------: | ---------: | -------------------: | ----------------------: | :-------------: | -----------------: | ------------------------------------------------- |
| **Dev – lean**                    | S1   |   1 |        1 |          1 |              **160** |        **~503,316,480** |        ❌        |         **245.28** | Use subset of data; same schema/settings as prod. |
| **Dev – full data (no HA)**       | S1   |   3 |        1 |          3 |              **480** |      **~1,509,949,440** |    ✅ (tight)    |         **735.84** | Mirrors prod storage; no HA.                      |
| **Prod – minimum (no HA)**        | S1   |   3 |        1 |          3 |              **480** |      **~1,509,949,440** |    ✅ (tight)    |         **735.84** | Meets storage/QPS minimal; single replica risk.   |
| **Prod – recommended (HA)**       | S1   |   6 |        2 |          3 |              **480** |      **~1,509,949,440** |    ✅ (tight)    |       **1,471.68** | HA (2 replicas), better throughput.               |
| **Prod – safer headroom (no HA)** | S1   |   4 |        1 |          4 |              **640** |      **~2,013,265,920** | ✅ (comfortable) |         **981.12** | ~47% extra storage headroom.                      |
| **Prod – safer headroom (HA)**    | S1   |   8 |        2 |          4 |              **640** |      **~2,013,265,920** | ✅ (comfortable) |       **1,962.24** | HA + comfortable headroom.                        |

**Why “tight”?**
Your estimated index size is ~**434 GB**. With **3 partitions (480 GB)** you have ~**46 GB (~9–10%)** headroom. Best practice is **15–20%** to absorb index overhead, rebuilds, analyzer changes, and growth. Hence the “safer headroom” 4-partition option.

---

### Quick Excel helper (paste these in cells)

* **Parameters**

  * `PricePerSU = 245.28`
  * `AvgDocKB = 0.333`
  * `Docs = 1365563219`
* **Derived**

  * `KBperPartition = 160*1024*1024`
  * `DocsPerPartition = KBperPartition / AvgDocKB`
  * `StorageNeededGB = (Docs * AvgDocKB) / (1024*1024)`
  * `PartitionsNeeded = CEILING(StorageNeededGB / 160, 1)`
  * `MonthlyCost = SUs * PricePerSU`

(For HA, set `SUs = Replicas * Partitions`.)

---

### What to say in the meeting (one-liner)

> “Our 1.36B docs (~434 GB) **fit in 3 partitions** on S1. That’s **3 SUs** minimum (~$736/mo) or **6 SUs** (~$1,472/mo) for HA. Because headroom is only ~10%, I recommend **4 partitions** for production if we expect growth or index changes (4 SUs no-HA or 8 SUs with HA).”
